  "published": "2021-07-09",
  "runtimeMin": 88,
  "format": "The first new MCU movie in 737 days, and Sean and Amanda split on whether a no-homework Bond riff counts as a Marvel event. Then Sean talks to Leigh Janiak about shooting the Fear Street trilogy back-to-back.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "‘Black Widow’",
      "note": "Sean Fennessey and Amanda Dobbins",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Black Widow",
          "year": 2021,
          "note": "Scarlett Johansson's eighth MCU appearance is her first solo lead, and it arrives as a period piece set in 2016 for a character Endgame already killed. Sean and Amanda agree it plays more like a Bond or Mission: Impossible movie than a Marvel one, a standalone with low stakes and no homework required. Florence Pugh's Yelena runs away with it; David Harbour's Red Guardian gets a broad Russian accent. The stinger, with Julia Louis-Dreyfus as Contessa Valentina Allegra de Fontaine, is the only real setup for what's next. Sean calls it two and a half stars, three for Pugh."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "interview",
      "heading": "Leigh Janiak on the Fear Street trilogy",
      "guest": "Leigh Janiak on",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Fear Street Part One: 1994",
          "year": 2021,
          "note": "First of the three, styled after '90s self-referential slashers: dolly track, crane work, needle drops Netflix paid to clear."
        },
        {
          "title": "Fear Street Part Two: 1978",
          "year": 2021,
          "note": "The summer-camp entry, shot with more Steadicam and fluid motion."
        },
        {
          "title": "Fear Street Part Three: 1666",
          "year": 2021,
          "note": "The one Janiak was most excited to shoot, all handheld. Three R-rated movies shot across 106 days from R.L. Stine's books, released on consecutive Fridays."
        },
        {
          "title": "Honeymoon",
          "year": 2014,
          "note": "Her 2014 debut, an intimate body-snatcher indie that got her into directing television."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
